{
  "stem": "18186.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we never exchanged a word with each other.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, there was another one from my town sitting, older than me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Never said one word, like we never knew each other.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For safety reasons, because if not, if I would start talking-- I mean, our Polish was good.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we still had a slight accent.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we couldn't-- we couldn't open our mouth-- my mouth, you know?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Or she couldn't open her mouth too.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we-- and we were afraid they should catch on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we didn't speak to each other, and the same thing when they took us back.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We didn't-- they dropped us off.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They dropped everybody who was picked up from-- from, you know, were dropped off at the same spot.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we went to-- to they dropped me off where they picked me up, to where the Polish family stayed.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was only like a couple days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then from there, we went to Schneidemuhl.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I went with the Polish family--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Schneidemuhl by train, and then when we get there, the same thing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They started to-- they-- we went through this, like I said before, we went through the doctors and this or checkup.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So they checked us out, if we're healthy.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And because if you're not healthy, they really didn't want you there.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They want people to-- to go to work.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And what-- well, the next morning, they told us to line up, who are all the newcomers.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the people came from the-- the-- the farmers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they were picking up families.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And my, the family, was a healthy-- healthy young people that-- the parents was still very young.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They had the children, two children, that they were able-- that could, the older son could work.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
